When determining what makes an individual person happy you must first determine what drives that person. You must determine if that person is driven by a passion for something they genuinely care about and if that is an individual passion or a passion driven from the outside by other individuals. To determine this, you must completely understand the person.
      Most people on this planet are inherently selfish. They typically want to do things that make them happy and only them happy. However, most individuals feel a special kind of purpose when they are able to help other people. I believe when it comes down to understanding whether people will be happier if they focus on their personal goals or happiness of other, an individual person must be put to the test. By this, a person should be put into a scenario where they have the opportunity to only help themselves or to help only another person. In this scenario, the given person will make a choice and that will be the only deciding factor of whether the person will be more likely to be happy helping themselves or others. In my opinion, there is no way to determine this other than providing a scenario for people. You will know once the decision is made in real time.
     People will often do things selfishly to please themselves over other indivduals. However, when faced with a decision and a situation where they have a chance to prove whether they want to be happy based on pleasing themselve or others, people may surprise you.
